---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dreamlake — Pablo Anttila">
  <main>
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/work">← All work</a>
    </nav>

    <header>
      <small>2018–2020</small>
      <h1>Dreamlake</h1>
      <p>Cruise Booking Platform</p>
    </header>

    <figure>
      <p>[Project screenshot]</p>
    </figure>

    <article>
      <h2>What</h2>
      <p>A commercial platform for online cruise agents and travel agencies in the Nordics. Dreamlake's clients include some of the region's major travel businesses, offering a modern approach to selling and converting cruises online.</p>

      <h2>My role</h2>
      <p>Senior Frontend Developer and UI/UX Designer in a fast-paced startup environment. Worked across internal and external web interfaces with a focus on conversion metrics and user experience.</p>

      <h2>What I built</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Main booking interface</strong> — Designed, tested, and measured the user journey for online cruise booking</li>
        <li><strong>Site search</strong> — Faceted search for cruise discovery</li>
        <li><strong>Checkout flow</strong> — Conversion-optimized booking process</li>
        <li><strong>CMS solution</strong> — Headless content management with Prismic, including training for content creators</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Process</h2>
      <p>Created understanding through exploration and user interviews. Used heatmaps, analytics, and collaborative workshops to map out the platform's main pages, sitemaps, and views.</p>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <p>
        {['React', 'Next.js', 'Prismic CMS', 'REST API', 'Analytics'].map(tech => (
          <code>{tech}</code>
        ))}
      </p>

      <h2>The challenge</h2>
      <p>Cruise booking is complex — multiple cabin types, itineraries, pricing tiers, and add-ons. The challenge was making this feel simple without hiding options. Every interaction had to build confidence, not confusion.</p>

      <h2>Outcome</h2>
      <p>[Pablo: Add conversion improvements, booking volume, or client wins if available.]</p>
    </article>

    <nav>
      <a href="/work/toca-boca">← Toca Boca</a>
      <a href="/work/tobii">Tobii →</a>
    </nav>
  </main>
</Layout>
